    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 578.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of April 17 (No. 377) has
                            been received, and I have pleasure in stating that your correspondence
                            with Earl Russell on the subject of a resort to the employment of
                            judicial process, in co-operation with the government of Great Britain,
                            to prevent the threatened violations of the neutrality laws of the
                            kingdom, is entirely satisfactory to the President.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
